mann, relative and conditional\nentropy; mutual information, (modified) entanglement and R\\'{e}nyi entropy. We\nconstruct explicit examples of generic off-diagonal exact and parametric\nsolutions describing stationary solitonic gravitational hierarchies and\ndeformations of black hole configurations. Finally, we show how Perelman's\nentropy and geometric thermodynamic values, and extensions to GIF and QGIF\nmodels can be computed for various new classes of exact solutions which cannot\nbe described following the Bekenstein-Hawking approach.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 28 Jun 2019 14:00:24 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 15 Jul 2019 13:40:21 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 8 Feb 2020 18:33:24 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 21 Dec 2021 23:06:11 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Sat, 22 Jan 2022 13:21:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-25"}
